# <div style="border: 2px solid #4CAF50; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
  üìù <strong>Lab 1: Using Data Classification and Sensitivity Labels in Microsoft Purview</strong>
</div>

---

## <div style="color: #2E8B57;">Objective</div>
Learn how to create, apply, and manage sensitivity labels and data classifications to protect organizational data within Microsoft Purview and Microsoft 365 environments.

---

## <div style="color: #2E8B57;">Prerequisites</div>
- Access to Microsoft Purview & Microsoft 365 Compliance Center
- Permissions: Compliance Administrator, Information Protection Administrator, or equivalent
- Basic understanding of data sensitivity and classification concepts

---

## <div style="color: #2E8B57;">Starter Files</div>
- <strong>Sensitivity Labels JSON Config:</strong> <code>sensitivity-labels.json</code> (sample JSON configuration for labels)
- <strong>Sample Data Files:</strong>
  - <code>Sample_Confidential_Document.docx</code>
  - <code>Sample_Public_Report.pdf</code>
- <em>Screenshot placeholders</em> for documentation

---

## <div style="color: #2E8B57;">Steps</div>

### 1. Sign in to Microsoft Purview & Compliance Center
- Navigate to <a href="https://compliance.microsoft.com" target="_blank">https://compliance.microsoft.com</a>
- Sign in with your admin account

---

### 2. Create Sensitivity Labels
**Option A:** Use the GUI to create labels
- Navigate: Data classification &gt; Sensitivity labels
- Click <strong>"+ Create a sensitivity label"</strong>
- Define labels such as:
  - <strong>Confidential</strong>
  - <strong>Internal Use Only</strong>
  - <strong>Public</strong>

**Option B:** Use JSON configuration (starter template provided below)

---

### 3. Sample JSON Configuration for Sensitivity Labels

```json
{
  "SensitivityLabels": [
    {
      "Name": "Confidential",
      "Description": "Highly sensitive data requiring encryption and restricted access",
      "Color": "Red",
      "Encryption": {
        "Enabled": true,
        "DefaultProtection": "EncryptOnly"
      },
      "ContentMarking": {
        "Watermark": "CONFIDENTIAL",
        "Header": null,
        "Footer": null
      }
    },
    {
      "Name": "Internal Use Only",
      "Description": "Internal data for organizational use",
      "Color": "Yellow",
      "Encryption": {
        "Enabled": false
      },
      "ContentMarking": {
        "Watermark": "INTERNAL USE ONLY",
        "Header": null,
        "Footer": null
      }
    },
    {
      "Name": "Public",
      "Description": "Publicly shareable data",
      "Color": "Green",
      "Encryption": {
        "Enabled": false
      },
      "ContentMarking": {
        "Watermark": null,
        "Header": null,
        "Footer": null
      }
    }
  ]
}
